The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Sept. 22: The government has cleared Nokia?s Rs 675-crore plan to set up a special economic zone near Chennai. It has also given in-principle approval to Reliance Energy?s 4000-hectare SEZ in Dadri, Reliance Industries?s petrochemical zone in Jamnagar and a biotechnology SEZ near Pune by Serum institute involving an investment of Rs 1,200 crore. It is also speeding up the notification of the SEZ act by November, said G.K. Pillai, additional secretary in the ministry of commerce.

 New Delhi, Sept. 22: The government today raised the subsidy rate for small-scale units from 12 per cent to 15 per cent. It has also raised the ceiling on loans under the credit linked capital subsidy scheme for SSIs to Rs 1 crore from Rs 40 lakh. The scheme will be valid till March 31, 2007.

 Bangalore, Sept. 22: Steel Authority of India and Vishakhapatnam steel plant may pick up equity in coking coal production ventures in Australia, Canada and China.

 Tokyo, Sept. 22: Electronics and entertainment conglomerate Sony Corp has said it would cut 7 per cent of its global work force, sell more than $1 billion in assets and post a loss this year.

 New Delhi, Sept. 22: Canada will support India in the WTO negotiations, especially in agriculture and services, said Canadian minister for international trade James Peterson.




